2026-03-26 05:36:47 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Philip Morris International Inc earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/food-beverage-tobacco/nyse-pm/philip-morris-international/future', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Future Growth - Simply Wall St', 'content': "Philip Morris International Inc.\n\nNYSE:PM Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$295.5b\n\n# Philip Morris International Future Growth\n\n## Future criteria checks 2/6\n\nPhilip Morris International is forecast to grow earnings and revenue by 8.4% and 6.4% per annum respectively. EPS is expected to grow by 8.7% per annum. Return on equity is forecast to be 1315.7% in 3 years.\n\n## Key information\n\n8.4%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n8.66%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Tobacco earnings growth | 7.6% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 6.4% |\n| Future return on equity | 1,315.67% |\n| Analyst coverage | Good |\n| Last updated | 19 Feb 2026 |\n\nGood\n\n## Recent future growth updates\n\n### Price target increased by 7.6% to US$194\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2026 [...] ## Analyst Future Growth Forecasts\n\nEarnings vs Savings Rate: PM's forecast earnings growth (8.4% per year) is above the savings rate (3.4%).\n\nEarnings vs Market: PM's earnings (8.4% per year) are forecast to grow slower than the US market (15.6% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Earnings: PM's earnings are forecast to grow, but not significantly.\n\nRevenue vs Market: PM's revenue (6.4% per year) is forecast to grow slower than the US market (10.3% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Revenue: PM's revenue (6.4% per year) is forecast to grow slower than 20% per year.\n\n## Earnings per Share Growth Forecasts\n\n## Future Return on Equity\n\nFuture ROE: PM's Return on Equity is forecast to be very high in 3 years time (1315.7%).\n\n## Discover growth companies\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y [...] | Date | Revenue | Earnings | Free Cash Flow | Cash from Op | Avg. No. Analysts |\n ---  ---  --- |\n| 12/31/2028 | 50,063 | 14,446 | 15,336 | 17,455 | 10 |\n| 12/31/2027 | 46,697 | 13,505 | 14,450 | 16,208 | 15 |\n| 12/31/2026 | 43,801 | 12,026 | N/A | 14,210 | 15 |\n| 12/31/2025 | 40,648 | 11,316 | 10,664 | 12,233 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2025 | 39,992 | 8,601 | 10,123 | 11,526 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2025 | 39,058 | 8,207 | 8,989 | 10,406 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2025 | 38,386 | 7,574 | 10,195 | 11,626 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2024 | 37,878 | 7,034 | 10,773 | 12,217 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2024 | 37,219 | 9,805 | 10,040 | 11,517 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2024 | 36,449 | 8,779 | 10,121 | 11,590 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2024 | 35,948 | 7,944 | 8,941 | 10,400 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2023 | 35,174 | 7,791 | 7,883 | 9,204 | N/A |", 'score': 0.9348309, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.morningstar.com/news/dow-jones/202602064776/philip-morris-posts-higher-4q-profit-revenue-forecasts-continued-growth', 'title': 'Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts Continued ...', 'content': "Morningstar\n\n# Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts Continued Growth\n\nBy Connor Hart\n\nPhilip Morris International logged higher profit and revenue in the fourth quarter, while forecasting continued growth for years to come.\n\nThe tobacco company--which sells cigarettes such as Marlboro and Parliament in overseas markets, as well as smokeless tobacco such as Zyn worldwide--posted operating income of $3.4 billion, up 3.5% from a year earlier. Earnings came in at $1.37 a share.\n\nStripping out certain one-time items, earnings were $1.70 a share. That was in line with analysts' expectations for adjusted earnings, according to FactSet.\n\nRevenue increased 6.8% to $10.36 billion, just below Wall Street views for $10.38 billion. [...] Total shipment volumes edged 0.1% higher to 193.8 billion units.\n\nChief Executive Jacek Olczak said 2025 marked the company's fifth consecutive year of volume growth, with results boosted by continued growth across its smoke-free business and operating margin expansion.\n\nFor the current quarter, the company expects adjusted earnings of $1.80 to $1.85 a share, compared with analyst views for $1.89 a share.\n\nLooking ahead, Philip Morris guided for earnings of $7.87 to $8.02 a share in 2026. On an adjusted basis, earnings are projected to come in between $8.38 and $8.53 a share. Analysts were looking for earnings of $8.01 a share, or $8.34 a share on an adjusted basis.\n\nThe forecast assumes net revenue growth of 5% to 7% for the year, as well as organic operating income growth of 7$ to 9%. [...] The company additionally disclosed its compounded annual growth targets through 2028, calling for a 6% to 8% increase for net revenues, an 8% to 10% increase for operating income, and a 9% to 11% increase for adjusted per-share earnings.\n\nWrite to Connor Hart at connor.hart@wsj.com\n\n(END) Dow Jones Newswires\n\nFebruary 06, 2026 07:53 ET (12:53 GMT)\n\nThe articles, information, and content displayed on this webpage may\ninclude materials prepared and provided by third parties. Such\nthird-party content is offered for informational purposes only and\nis not endorsed, reviewed, or verified by Morningstar.", 'score': 0.933969, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.gurufocus.com/news/8626580/philip-morris-pm-reaffirms-2026-earnings-forecast', 'title': 'Philip Morris (PM) Reaffirms 2026 Earnings Forecast - GuruFocus', 'content': "Philip Morris International (PM) is set to discuss its strategic outlook at the 2026 Consumer Analyst Group of New York Conference, scheduled for 10:00 a.m. ET. The company has reiterated its full-year 2026 earnings per share (EPS) projection, initially announced on February 6th, ranging from $7.87 to $8.02.\n\nWhen adjustments amounting to $0.51 per share are excluded, the adjusted diluted EPS is anticipated to be between $8.38 and $8.53. This forecasted range marks an expected increase of 11.1% to 13.1% compared to the $7.54 EPS reported in 2025. Furthermore, excluding the positive effect of currency fluctuations at current exchange rates, which is valued at $0.27 per share, the growth is projected to be within 7.5% to 9.5%. [...] Philip Morris International operates within the Consumer Defensive sector, specifically in the Tobacco Products industry. The company boasts a substantial market capitalization of $285.88 billion, reflecting its significant influence and stability within the market.\n\n## Financial Health Analysis\n\nPhilip Morris International has demonstrated consistent revenue growth, with a 3-year revenue growth rate of 8.4%. The company's profitability is underscored by its impressive operating margin of 36.74% and a net margin of 27.92%. These figures highlight the company's ability to efficiently manage its operations and maintain a strong bottom line. [...] 🚀 Enjoy a 7-Day Free Trial Thru Mar 30, 2026! ✨\n\n0\n\n   \n\n7-Day Free Trial\n\n/\n\nCFG\n\n▼0.05%\n\nGURUFOCUS.COM  Latest News USA Tobacco Products  PM\n\n# Philip Morris (PM) Reaffirms 2026 Earnings Forecast\n\n \n\nAuthor's Avatar\n\nGuruFocus News\n\n02/18/2026 07:55\n\nKey Takeaways:\n\n## PM GF Value™: $133.6\n\nModestly Overvalued\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc\n\n Download Chart\n Download Data premium\n\nView Full PM Analysis →\n\n Philip Morris International PM -0.16%\n\n  86 is reaffirming its strategic outlook with a focus on robust earnings growth for 2026.\n The company projects an adjusted diluted EPS increase of 11.1% to 13.1% for 2026, excluding currency impacts.\n Philip Morris International maintains a strong market position in the tobacco industry, bolstered by its acquisition of Swedish Match.", 'score': 0.90692574, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.tradingview.com/news/tradingview:168c3bfea5aba:0-philip-morris-international-reports-2025-fourth-quarter-full-year-results/', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year ...', 'content': "Future Outlook\n\n \n\nPMI provided a full-year 2026 forecast with reported diluted EPS expected to be in the range of $7.87 to $8.02. The company also set compound annual growth targets for 2026-2028, aiming for 6% to 8% net revenue growth, 8% to 10% operating income growth, and 9% to 11% adjusted diluted EPS growth, excluding currency impacts.\n\nOriginal SEC Filing: [Philip Morris International Inc. [ PM ] - 8-K - Feb. 06, 2026](\n\nDisclaimer\n\nThis is an AI-powered summary. It may contain inaccuracies. Consider verifying important information with the source. Please note this summary is solely based on documents filed with the SEC.\n\nEarningsTradingViewUS stocks\n\n## More news from TradingView [...] Get started\n\nTradingViewTradingView\n\n# Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year Results\n\n2 min read\n\nPM\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc. (PMI) has released its financial results for the fourth quarter and full year of 2025. The company reported significant growth in its smoke-free product (SFP) segment, contributing to overall revenue and profit increases. The report also includes forward-looking statements and growth targets for the upcoming years.\n\n \n\nFinancial Highlights [...] Financial Highlights\n\n \n\nFor the full year 2025, PMI reported a diluted EPS of $7.26, a substantial increase from $4.52 in 2024. The adjusted diluted EPS was $7.54, representing a growth of 14.8%, and 14.2% on a currency-neutral basis. Net revenues surpassed $40 billion, with the smoke-free business contributing close to $17 billion. The company's gross profit increased by 11.1% to $27.3 billion.\n\n \n\nBusiness and Operational Highlights", 'score': 0.88444936, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.pmi.com/media-center/press-releases/press-details/?newsId=29236', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Third-Quarter & First Nine ...', 'content': 'Reported diluted EPS is forec