2026-03-26 05:37:50 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Addus HomeCare Corporation earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://www.investing.com/news/earnings/addus-homecare-earnings-up-next-as-investors-eye-acquisition-talk-93CH-4519232', 'title': 'Addus HomeCare earnings up next as investors eye acquisition talk', 'content': '# Addus HomeCare earnings up next as investors eye acquisition talk\n\nBy\n\nEarnings\n\nPublished 02/23/2026, 10:04 AM\n\nAddus HomeCare earnings up next as investors eye acquisition talk\n\nView all comments (0)0\n\n&copy; Reuters.\n\n© Reuters.\n\nADUS-0.74%\n\nAddus HomeCare Corporation reports fourth-quarter results Monday after the market close, with analysts expecting the home healthcare provider to post another quarter of robust growth—and watching closely for signals on potential deal-making.\n\nAnalysts project revenue of $372.9 million, up 25.5% year over year, and earnings of $1.72 per share, representing a 24.6% increase from the prior year. If the company meets forecasts, it would mark sequential gains from the third quarter, when Addus posted EPS of $1.56 and revenue of $362.3 million. [...] Recent Performance\n\nIn the third quarter, Addus beat analysts’ revenue expectations with $362.3 million, up 25% year over year, and also exceeded EPS estimates. The company has delivered consistent execution, though it has missed Wall Street’s revenue estimates multiple times over the last two years.\n\nThe home healthcare sector faces both opportunities and challenges heading into 2026. Demand for home-based services remains strong as the aging population grows and healthcare delivery continues moving closer to the home, but workforce shortages continue to challenge agencies by increasing labor costs and limiting service capacity.\n\nFor Addus, Monday’s report will test whether the company can sustain its growth trajectory while providing the strategic clarity investors are seeking. [...] Balance sheet strength gives Addus flexibility to pursue deals. The company carries a net debt-to-EBITDA ratio of just 0.3x, and Citizens analyst Constantine Davides expects Addus to generate approximately $140 million in free cash flow in 2026, positioning it well for "accretive acquisitions."\n\nOperationally, analysts anticipate fourth-quarter results will be roughly in line with expectations, with the potential for a modest EBITDA beat and continued improvement in same-store volume trends—key indicators of business momentum.\n\nRecent Performance', 'score': 0.99999714, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.itiger.com/news/1153192929', 'title': "Addus HomeCare this quarter's revenue is expected to increase by ...", 'content': 'Based on the latest compiled expectations, Addus HomeCare’s fourth-quarter revenue is projected at $372.31 million, representing 27.71% year-over-year growth, with adjusted EPS forecast at 1.73, implying a 28.09% increase year over year. Consensus forecasts for gross profit margin and net profit or net margin are not explicitly available, while EBIT is estimated at $44.04 million, up 31.00% year over year. The company’s core operations remain driven by scale in recurring services, and the outlook frames further growth supported by ongoing execution and cost discipline implied by the consensus trajectory for revenue and EBIT. Among operating lines, the largest revenue base provides visibility for continued contribution this quarter, while segment mix will remain an important lens through [...] EPS forecast. The constructive stance also reflects comfort with the sequential improvements in profitability, including a 3.61% quarter-over-quarter increase in net profit last quarter, which helps anchor sentiment around sustained operating momentum. Overall, the preponderance of analyst commentary aligns with a positive setup, predicated on the company meeting consensus revenue and EBIT forecasts and demonstrating continued discipline in translating growth into earnings. [...] the prior quarter. Execution that meets this profile would underpin the EPS forecast of 1.73, while a mix shift toward more cost-intensive episodes could temper the translation of revenue growth into earnings.', 'score': 0.99999225, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20260223140576/en/Addus-HomeCare-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-and-Year-End-2025-Financial-Results', 'title': 'Addus HomeCare Announces Fourth Quarter and Year End 2025 ...', 'content': '“Our personal care business has been the key driver of our growth and accounted for 76.6% of our revenues for the fourth quarter. The 6.3% organic revenue growth in our personal care business was supported by strong volumes as well as higher rates in certain key markets compared with the same period last year. These results also include the personal care operations of Del Cielo Home Care Services (“Del Cielo”), which we acquired on October 1, 2025. [...] For the full year 2025, net service revenues increased 23.2% to $1.42 billion from $1.15 billion for the prior-year period. Net income was $95.9 million for 2025 compared with $73.6 million for 2024, and net income per diluted share was $5.22 compared with $4.23 per diluted share. Adjusted EBITDA increased 28.3% to $180.0 million for 2025 from $140.3 million for 2024. Adjusted net income was $114.7 million for 2025 compared with $91.4 million for 2024, while adjusted net income per diluted share was $6.23 compared with $5.26 for the prior-year period. [...] Commenting on the results, Dirk Allison, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, said, “Our fourth quarter results marked a strong finish to a successful year of growth and progress for Addus. Net service revenues increased 25.6% and adjusted EBITDA was up 33.3% over the fourth quarter of 2024. For the full year, we achieved a new annual record of $1.4 billion in net service revenues, an increase of 23.2% compared with 2024. Continued strong demand has supported this impressive growth as an increasing number of consumers and payers benefit from the value and cost efficiency offered by our home-based care services. With solid execution, our team has done an outstanding job meeting this demand with the ability to leverage our scale and proven operating model across the care continuum. We have', 'score': 0.9999895, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://investor.wedbush.com/wedbush/article/stockstory-2026-2-22-addus-homecare-earnings-what-to-look-for-from-adus', 'title': 'Addus HomeCare Earnings: What To Look For From ADUS', 'content': 'The euphoria surrounding Trump’s November win lit a fire under major indices, but potential tariffs have caused the market to do a 180 in 2025. While some of the healthcare providers & services stocks have shown solid performance in this choppy environment, the group has generally underperformed, with share prices down 3.2% on average over the last month. Addus HomeCare is up 4.6% during the same time and is heading into earnings with an average analyst price target of $141 (compared to the current share price of $115.45). [...] Looking at Addus HomeCare’s peers in the healthcare providers & services segment, some have already reported their Q4 results, giving us a hint as to what we can expect. Brookdale’s revenues decreased 3.4% year on year, missing analysts’ expectations by 1.7%, and Guardant Health reported revenues up 39.4%, topping estimates by 3.5%. Brookdale traded down 9.7% following the results while Guardant Health was also down 3.1%.\n\nRead our full analysis of Brookdale’s results here and Guardant Health’s results here. [...] Is Addus HomeCare a buy or sell going into earnings? Read our full analysis here, it’s free for active Edge members.\n\nThis quarter, the market is expecting Addus HomeCare’s revenue to grow 25.5% year on year, improving from the 7.5% increase it recorded in the same quarter last year