ooking ahead, Verizon provided an optimistic outlook for 2026, projecting adjusted EPS of $4.90 to $4.95, well above the analyst consensus of $4.76. The company expects total retail postpaid phone net additions of 750,000 to 1.0 million and total mobility and broadband service revenue growth of 2.0% to 3.0%.', 'score': 0.9994967, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://stocktwits.com/news-articles/markets/equity/verizon-stock-jumps-2026-guidance-subscriber-growth/cmyS0JiR4SG', 'title': 'Verizon Projects Sharper Customer Growth, Revenue In ...', 'content': 'Shivani Kumaresan·Stocktwits\n\n Updated Mar 05, 2026   |   2:29 PM EST\n\nShare·Add us on\n\n Verizon sees retail postpaid phone net additions in 2026 to be between 750,000 and 1 million, roughly two to three times the level reported in 2025.\n The company also expects broadband and mobility service revenue to rise by about 2% to 3%, to nearly $93 billion.\n For Q1, the company reported a revenue of $36.4 billion with an adjusted EPS of $1.09.\n\nVerizon Communications Inc. (VZ) on Friday outlined 2026 expectations, suggesting a sharp increase in customer additions and solid earnings growth as the telecommunications company builds on momentum from a strong finish to 2025.\n\nThe company provided a 2026 outlook following its fourth-quarter (Q4) and full-year 2025 earnings.\n\n## Customer Growth [...] ## Customer Growth\n\nVerizon sees retail postpaid phone net additions in 2026 to be between 750,000 and 1 million, roughly two to three times the level reported in 2025, marking a sign of renewed traction.\n\nThe company also expects broadband and mobility service revenue to rise by about 2% to 3%, to near $93 billion, even as traditional wireless service revenue growth remains flat.\n\nVerizon anticipates adjusted earnings per share (EPS) in the range of $4.90 to $4.95, reflecting a 4%–5% improvement year over year (YoY).\n\nFollowing the update, Verizon stock traded over 4% higher in Friday’s premarket. On Stocktwit